name: Brooklyn Cycle
description:
Brooklyn garages were the homes to many a grease monkey. Neighborhood youth would gather and compete with their hot rods and fast motorcycles. Then meet at the local soda fountain to exchange bragging rights.
This tee is tribute to those grease monkeys, the Brooklyn mechanics who were once kings of anything with a motor!
This vintage design is printed on a black cotton tee in white ink.

name: Coney Island Devil
description:
The Mysterious smiling Duke of Brooklyn residing in spirit at Coney Island. He is surrounded by his burlesque sirens in a vintage tattoo style tee.
Printed in a tri-blend super soft tee with black ink.

name: Coney Island Mermaid Women's
description: The Brooklyn Mermaid found in the seas at Coney Island! Vintage tattoo style with nautical star on the sleeve. Protector of drunken sailors and the rum that gets 'em there!

name: Shark Girl
description:
A Sailor girl in her Girlie sailor attire, taming a shark, a Brooklyn shark. But since she's a Brooklyn chick, my money's on her! 
Printed on a soft grey cotton tee with black ink.

name: Brooklyn Anchor
description:
Drop anchor here in Brooklyn and search for ye fortune! Treasure and mermaids abound...
Printed on a silver grey cotton tee in black ink.
Available for men and women!

name: Coney Island Mermaid Men's
description:
I hear Coney Island is famous for it's Mermaid population...but they can't catch this one! Protector of her fellow sea sirens and drunken sailors, in vintage flash style.
This one is for the dude...
Printed on a heather soft blue tee with black ink.

name: Tattoo Girl
description:
Here she is, clever girl, tattoo'd, at sea and ready to conquer!
Printed on an oatmeal (light heather cream color) tee with black ink.

name: Brooklyn Anchor Black Tee
description:
Drop anchor here in Brooklyn and search for ye fortune! Treasure and mermaids abound... 
Printed on a black cotton tee with white ink. 
Available for men and women!

name: Ahoy Sailor
description: A sailor girl off to sea to protect her country and conspire with her sister Mermaids of the deep.

name: Brooklyn to the Bone
description:
The bulldog, the face of Brooklyn and the attitude that runs deep!  Stubborn and tough yet true to the bone!
Vintage tattoo style tee, printed on a black all cotton tee with white ink.

name: Cowgirl
description:
Tough and ready cowgirl designed in vintage tattoo style.
She'll lasso your heart!
Printed on a banana yellow cotton tee with dark brown ink.

name: Sailor Boy
description:
Vintage Sailor Boy on leave struttin' his stuff! 
Printed on a navy blue men's all cotton tee with white ink.

name: Jack
description:
This is my homage to Jack, the coolest next to Clint Eastwood and DeNiro that is...From the movie, "The Last Detail", 1973. 
Printed on a cotton heather grey tee with black ink.

name: Red Hook Anchor
description:
Honoring Red Hook, Brooklyn where the longshoremen of the past toiled her harbor. We celebrate the pioneers of Red Hook who live in her vulnerable seaside life.
Printed on a dark grey cotton tee with black ink.

name: Gowanus Swim Team
description:
The infamous Gowanus Canal as a swim team emblem! Through toxic water and floods, we will swim! The Black Lagoon ain't got nuthin' on us! What happens in the canal, stays in the canal...
This navy cotton tee is printed with gold ink in distressed style!

name: The Coney Island Shore Theater
description:
This is the Coney Island Shore Theater, which has been landmarked. A beautiful building left to us from the old classic Coney Island! Sadly, it's large, iconic sign was recently destroyed in hurricane Sandy.
Printed on a warm grey cotton tee with black ink.

name: Stiletto Love
description:
Ah, the classic and promising Stiletto, if they could only talk!
Printed on a saucy red cotton tee with black ink.

name: The Gowanus Skate Club
description:
Ah Brooklyn athletics...swimming and kayaking in the Gowanus Canal and now The Gowanus has a skate club! 
Classic Brooklyn always had roller skating so we need to bring it back! And Brooklyn does...at the Brooklyn Lyceum in Park Slope, Bklyn!
Black cotton tee printed with gold ink.
ALSO available, the black women's TANK top, printed with gold ink.

name: Domino Sugar Tee
description:
The Domino Sugar Refinery in Brooklyn, one of the oldest buildings in Brooklyn, located in Williamsburg, was the original refinery of the American Sugar Refining Company, which produced Domino brand sugar.
The current complex dates from 1882, when it was the largest sugar refinery in the world. Several of the buildings in the complex were given landmark status in 2007.
This is a vintage logo from Domino Sugar created from the woodblock that was used in the past to print labels for the sugar.
Printed on a Olive clored cotton tee.

name: Old Brooklyn Dodgers
description:
Brooklyn's own baseball team from 1884 until 1957, after which it moved to Los Angeles. 
This is the original Logo of the Brooklyn Dodgers from 1910 through 1913.
Printed on a heather grey tee with blue ink.

name: Brooklyn Dodger Baseball Tee
description:
I'd like to introduce my tribute to the Brooklyn Dodgers. This design is based on a pin they would sell in the late 1950's at Ebbet's Field, Brooklyn. 
Printed on heather grey with royal blue ink.

name: Brooklyn Dodger Baseball Tee/Navy
description:
I'd like to introduce my tribute to the Brooklyn Dodgers. This design is based on a pin they would sell in the late 1950's at Ebbet's Field, Brooklyn. 
Printed on a cotton navy blue tee with white ink.

name: Lunacy
description:
The moon is a dapper Gentleman of the evening watching over the lovers and those who look to the sky and wish for Love. 
Printed on a heathered sage tee with black ink.

name: The Gentleman and His Peacock
description:
The avant garde Gentleman, a glass of champagne and his Peacock... 
not to forget, the lobster. 
Black coton tee printed with white ink.

name: The Fortune Teller
description:
See the Fortune Teller with your questions about Love and Life, he knows the stars and will read your cards. 
Cardinal red tee printed with black ink, very soft.

name: Joker's Wild Card
description:
One clown side up holding a magic rose he's just pulled out of his sleeve. The image, two vintage looking clowns designed as a playing card offering up their sweet style of magic and humor. They appear on a joker's card. 
Printed in black ink on a dark grey heathered tee.

name: The Tarot Card/red
description:
A beautiful vintage Tarot card back image that reflects the yearnings of the soul! 
Printed in black ink on a red tee, 100% cotton and very soft fabric and comfortable fit.

name: The Tarot Card/black
description:
A beautiful vintage Tarot card back image that reflects the yearnings of the soul! 
Printed with white ink on a black tee, 100% cotton and very soft fabric and comfortable fit.

name: The Swine Economist
description:
The portly pig businessman, in vintage garb, reading the financial page, contemplating whether he should invest in Tofu Futures...in an alternate universe perhaps? 
Printed on a cream colored tee in black ink.

name: Hoedown Showdown
description:
Two former enemies, a Bear and his new buddy, the Bull, dancing in a country hoe down, celebrating their peace!! 
This design is printed on a light olive tee in black ink, a beautiful fit and very soft to the touch.

name: King and Queen of Rock
description:
Vintage playing card combining the King and the Queen card as one and as the new monarchy of Rock n' Roll!
Men's tees are printed King side up and the women's tee is printed Queen side up! 
Printed on a cardinal red heathered cotton tee, incredibly soft with black ink.

name: The Joker
description:
A Vintage Joker, relaxed and performing for the amusement of the Royal Court, holding his courtly scepter. 
Printed on a sage heathered tee with black ink.

name: The Fool
description:
The happy Fool out and about alone playing with the Moon and leaving a wake of stardust! 
Printed on a warm, deep grey cotton tee with black ink.

name: Lion Coffee
description:
Lion Coffee, an old coffee company no longer around, leaving us this beautiful advertising design which I have artfully altered and enhanced. 
Printed on a cream cotton tee in black ink.

name: Coney Island Mermaid Baby Pink
description:
Babies are the closest we got to being a true Mermaid or Merman.
They are natural swimmers. And I hear they they're all from Coney Island first and then seagulls take them to their new Mommies and Daddies...!
Fuchsia cotton onesie with our Mermaid and anchor printed in squid black ink. Yes I said SQUID, they secrete black ink...no I don't really use squid ink but I should...

name: Coney Island Mermaid Baby Blue
description:
Babies are the closest we got to being a true Mermaid or Merman.
They are natural swimmers. And I hear they they're all from Coney Island first and then seagulls take them to their new Mommies and Daddies...!
Turquoise cotton ONESIE with our Mermaid and anchor printed in squid black ink. Yes I said SQUID, they secrete black ink...no I don't really use squid ink but I should...

name: Coney Island Mermaid/baby girl
description:
This little girl is a mermaid in training! Getting her 'sea legs' under Mermaid Momma's careful watch...
Printed with black ink on a fuchsia one piece.
'

name: Anchor Baby
description:
Drop anchor here in Brooklyn and search for ye fortune! Treasure and mermaids abound...and lots of babies too! We love the little bilge rats...!
Printed on heather grey with the black blood of the squid...ok black ink.

name: Sailor Boy Baby - Aqua
description:
Vintage Sailor Boy on leave struttin' his stuff! For all the little sailors  who love the sea!
Printed on an cotton aqua onesie with navy ink.

name: Shark Girl Baby
description:
A Sailor girl in her Girlie sailor attire, taming a shark, a Brooklyn shark. But since she's a Brooklyn chick, my money's on her! 
Printed on a soft grey cotton onesie with black ink.

name: Sailor Boy Baby
description:
Vintage Sailor Boy on leave struttin' his stuff! For all the little sailors  who love the sea!
Printed on a cotton navy oneise with white ink.

name: Brooklyn to the Bone/baby
description: Brooklyn is a tough spirit that runs deep and has grown in legend and force throughout many generations. New babies are handed over the Brooklyn attitude and can now tell those Jersey babies to back off...!

name: Tattoo Girl/baby
description:
Mamma of the Sea! Beautiful sea maven encased in a ship's wheel.
Baby can rock his or her nautical Mom!
Printed on a grey heather one piece with black ink.

name: The Big Fish
description:
A fox carrying his big prize fish! 
Printed with navy ink on a cotton mint green one piece.

name: Butterfly Tattoo Baby
description:
Baby can now share tattoos with her proud inked parents!
Heart with wings and stars.
Printed with black ink on a cotton fuchsia one piece.

name: The Three Piggies
description:
This is a vintage design of the 3 little Piggies playing their musical instruments.
Two color, red and black printed on a gold one piece.

name: Sir Moon
description:
Babies sleep tight for the moon is watching  and softly humming a lullaby.
Printed in black ink on a lavender one piece.

name: The Fool & Moon at Play
description:
This is a beautiful moment where the Fool is playing with the Moon and leaving a trail of stardust.
Printed with black ink on a soft banana yellow cotton tee.

name: Brooklyn Skate Baby
description:
Brooklyn has quite the roller skating heritage, the last to close in 2007 was located on Empire Blvd. in Flatbush called The Empire Rollerdrome. It was a Disco Roller skating rink.
Now we've got baby primed for his or her future in the new roller rinks of the future, in Brooklyn of course! Roller skating at the Brooklyn Lyceum, in Park Slope!
Gold ink printed on a cotton navy blue one piece.

name: Brooklyn Skate Baby/gold
description:
Brooklyn has quite the roller skating heritage, the last to close in 2007 was located on Empire Blvd. in Flatbush called The Empire Rollerdrome. It was a Disco Roller skating rink.
Now we've got baby primed for his or her future in the new roller rinks of the future, in Brooklyn of course! Roller skating at the Brooklyn Lyceum, in Park Slope!

name: Halloween Kitty
description:
Hey parental units this is a vintage inspired design for babies who want to rock Halloween too!
Printed with black ink on a gold cotton onesie.

name: The Pumpkin Cowboy
description: Saddle up for Halloween partners, this pumpkin is the new sheriff in town! Vintage Halloween design for baby printed on an orange cotton onesie.

name: Halloween Witch
description:
Ah the classic and tricky witch will never leave our Halloween style!
This is a vintage piece of art, re-designed with her old flavor and now brought to baby. Printed on a gold cotton one piece with water based black ghoulish ink...

name: Halloween Owl
description:
Spooky but happy Owl for baby's Halloween Trick or Treat!
Original design printed on an orange cotton onesie with dark brown ink.

name: The Tarot Card
description:
A beautiful Tarot card back design inspired by a vintage tarot card. Design and colors that reflect the yearnings of the soul! 
Amazing color!
Digital print on heavy weight, archival paper, 8" x 10", 11"x 17" and 13" x 19".

name: The Fortune Teller Print
description:
Ask a question, the Fortune Teller sees and knows all! 
Original design with vintage imagery. Digitally printed on beautiful, heavy weight archival paper, approximately 11" x 17". Also available on 8"x 10" and 13"x 19".

name: Tarot Card II
description:

Amazing color!
Digital print on heavy weight, archival paper, 8" x 10", 11"x 17"
and also available on 13" x 19".

name: Moon Over the Brooklyn Bridge
description:
This is an original design with vintage elements in Steampunk fashion where the old industrial world is revered and reinvented with it's original beauty. 
Digitally printed on heavy weight archival paper.
Approximately in 8" x 10", 12" x 17" and 13" x 19".

name: Joker's Wild Card Print
description:
Two vintage looking clowns designed as a playing card offering up their sweet style of magic and humor. They appear on a joker's card, with heart of course! 
Can be displayed either side up.
Digitally printed on heavy weight, archival paper.
Available in 8" x 10", 11" x 17" and on 13" x 19".

name: Lunacy Print
description:
The dimensions of time and space, confused in Lunacy or in reality? Make your own conclusions. 
Original design with vintage imagery.
Digitally printed on heavy weight, archival paper, 8" x 10", 
11" x 17", and 13" x 19".

name: Coney Island Devil Print
description:
The mysterious smiling duke of Brooklyn residing in Coney Island surrounded by his burlesque sirens in vintage tattoo style. 
This is an original design that is printed on heavy weight archival paper.
Approximately 11" x 17". Also available in 8" x 10" and 13" x 19".

name: Lion Coffee Print
description:
Here's an old vintage Coffee ad! The Lion is portrayed as robust as the coffee. Coffee is still an art. 
Printed on heavy weight, archival paper, approximately 11.5" x 16".
Also available on 8" x 10" and 13" x 19".
All prints hand signed!

name: Hoe Down Show Down
description:
Two former enemies, a Bear and a Bull, dancing in a country hoe down, celebrating their peace!! 
Digitally printed on heavy weight, archival paper. Image is 11" x 14".
Available on 8" x 10" , 11" x17" and 13" x 19".
All prints hand signed!
